blackbox
------------------------------------------
Blackbox is a fast, lightweight window manager for the X Window System, 
without all those annoying library dependencies. Blackbox is built with 
C++ and contains completely original code (even though the graphics 
implementation is similar to that of WindowMaker).

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.5.25-15
  libiconv2-1.12-1
  libX11_6-1.1.5-1
  libXext6-1.0.4-1
  libXft2-2.1.13-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf2.5-2.63-1
  automake1.9-1.9.6-3
  binutils-20080624-2
  cygport-0.4.2-1
  gawk-3.1.6-1
  gcc-core-3.4.4-3
  gcc-g++-3.4.4-3
  libtool-2.2.6a-1
  make-3.81-1
  pkg-config-0.23a-2
  sed-4.1.5-2

Canonical website:
  http://blackboxwm.sourceforge.net/

Canonical download:
  http://downloads.sourceforge.net/blackboxwm/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack blackbox-0.70.1-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./blackbox-0.70.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/blackbox-0.70.1-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/blackbox-0.70.1-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libbt-devel-0.70.1-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libbt0-0.70.1-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

